<item>
            <title>[OAK-1406] Background operations block writes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1406</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The background operations thread in DocumentNodeStore blocks writes to ensure a correct sequence of revisions introduced by local and external commits. Within this synchronization block the thread also invalidates caches.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1156&quot; title=&quot;Improve the document cache invalidation logic to selectivly invalidate doc&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1156&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1156&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a selective cache invalidation logic, which only invalidates documents that changed, but also comes with additional cost because it will make calls to MongoDB.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12694242">OAK-1406</key>
            <summary>Background operations block writes</summary>
